<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Position Relative/Absolute</title>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="../css/position.css">
    <style>
		
			.navigation {
				display: inline;
        width:100px;
        top:12px;
        left:-200;
				position: relative;
			}
		
			.contextMenu {
				position: absolute;
				top: 70%;
				left: 70%;
				width: 20vw;
				height: 10vh;
				display: none;
			}
			
			.navigation:hover > .contextMenu {
				display: inline;
			}
		
		</style>
  </head>
  <body> Hier versteckt sich ein Kontext-Menu:
    <div class="navigation">===
      <div class="contextMenu">Ein Kontext-Menu</div>
    </div>
    . Und danach geht es ganz normal weiter.
  </body>
</html>
